<br>
Sure....Sladen is right. I duo with a shammy alot because he says silly stupid things that make me laff. We joined the Endless together and now that that guild unfortunately has disbanded, we will probably head off to the same guild...whatever that might be. It's all about company and comraderie....or it should be. <br>
<br>
But Everquest and MMORPG's is about making new friends too and making friends in the first place. <br>
<br>
I would submit that the views underlying alot of the lack of favor for wizards in normal exp groups is based on substantive and important class balancing that needs to be addressed BECAUSE the end should be a game design that does not work against a given class in terms of their group friendliness.<br>
<br>
We want the same things Sam. Some of us just see some usefulness in class balancing in helping us make Everquest be &quot;all it can be&quot; in terms of fun, games, and comraderie with other people. <br>
<br>
Anecdotally....Last night spent 2 hours LFG in Velks. My first real brush with a lengthy LFG experience. You must wonder how my amazing persona can be conveyed to those people if my class gets in the way of me ever being invited to their group in the first place......<br>
<br>
Laters.<br>
<br>
Goanad<br>
54 Channeler<br>
